about.summary: SigClust is a statistical method for testing the significance of clustering results. SigClust can be applied to assess the statistical significance of splitting a data set into two clusters. For more than two clusters, SigClust can be used iteratively.

name: r-sigclust
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '1.1.0' %}

{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-sigclust
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  fn: sigclust_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url:
    - https://cran.r-project.org/src/contrib/sigclust_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - https://cran.r-project.org/src/contrib/Archive/sigclust/sigclust_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: efc4d8b8a19208efee9e86bbfd1aec09cac4fe3340033992f59e5892e9d9a104

build:
  noarch: generic
  number: 1002
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - r-base

  run:
    - r-base

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('sigclust')"  # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('sigclust')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=sigclust
  license: GPL (>= 2)
  summary: SigClust is a statistical method for testing the significance of clustering results.
    SigClust can be applied to assess the statistical significance of splitting a data
    set into two clusters. For more than two clusters, SigClust can be used iteratively.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3'  # [unix]
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}\R\share\licenses\GPL-3'  # [win]

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - dpryan79
    - cbrueffer
    - johanneskoester
    - bgruening
    - daler
    - jdblischak
